==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semitone
<hw>Sem"i*tone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>semi-</ets> + <ets>tone</ets>. CF. <er>Hemitone</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Half a tone; -- the name commonly applied to the
smaller intervals of the diatonic scale.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ There is an impropriety in the use of this word, and
<xex>half step</xex> is now preferred. See <er>Tone</er>.</note>
<rj><au>J. S. Dwight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semitonic</ent>⟦br⟧
